    "comment": "Rationale: Fig 2B: VAC14 puncta partially colocalized with both EEA1 (23±12%) and LAMP1 (29±9%) in neurites.\nFig 2C: VAC14 also colocalises with presynaptic terminal markers synapsin, synaptotagmin and VAMP/synaptobrevin.\nFig S7D-E: The specificity of VAC14 is demonstrated by the lack of staining in VAC14 -/- KO neurons.\nFigure S1A: Specificity of anti-VAC14 antibody was verified by the absence of a band in VAC14 KO brain lysates.. Experimental description: No information on which species the hippocampal neurons are derived from. 30/09/2020 Dnyanada: Authors were contacted for species information at ude.hcimu@namsiewl",
